post_text:
From my daughter's teacher tonight;
"Monday is Open Classroom game day. Kids are encouraged to wear their pajamas to school and bring a game or activity they can share with their friends. Game day has been an OC tradition for many years. I like having game day after the break, because it helps with the transition of being back in school. We are able to come back together as a community. The kids are able to reconnect with friends and spend time together talking about their winter break. We will have game day time in the morning and in the afternoon."

I'm glad we get to be at a school that puts the needs of students first.

